symbol.title: Ignore entire layer when generating stitch plan

g.aria-label: Do not use for sharp edges
For small edges. Depending on the fabric, you might need a pull compensation for the "cap".
For wide edges. The last stitch should point to the top.
This method interlocks the edges. The stitch angle needs to be equal for best results.

use.inkscape:label: Ink/Stitch Command: Ignore layer (do not stitch any objects in this layer)
